@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
<hr>
<div class="container mt-3">
    <p>This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose information about our users. By using our platform, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.</p>

    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4>Information we collect</h4>
            <p>We collect the following information from our users: first name, middle name, last name, age, email, password, address (optional), and phone number (optional). We collect this information to provide services such as attempting tests, reading lessons, and making assignments.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4>Information sharing</h4>
            <p>We only share user information with administrators of the platform. User information will not be shared with any third-party advertisers or service providers.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4>Information security</h4>
            <p>We take measures to protect user information from unauthorized access, disclosure, or misuse. User passwords are stored using SHA256 encryption and we use ASP.NET Identity for user authentication.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4>Data retention and deletion</h4>
            <p>We will retain user information for as long as necessary to provide the requested services or as required by law. We do not have a policy or procedure for deleting user data at this time.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4>User rights</h4>
            <p>Our platform provides users with the following rights regarding their personal information:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>The right to access their personal information</li>
                <li>The right to correct inaccurate personal information</li>
                <li>The right to request deletion of their personal information</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4>Opt-out options</h4>
            <p>Users can choose not to share their personal information by not signing up for an account or not enrolling in a course.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4>Data protection laws</h4>
            <p>We are subject to data protection laws, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA).</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4>Cookies</h4>
            <p>We use cookies to store login information for users.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4>Additional considerations</h4>
            <p>Our platform provides four different user roles: admin, teacher, user, and guest. Guest users cannot access courses, while user roles can access courses. Teachers can create courses, tests, and other content, while admin roles can manage user accounts.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
    @section Scripts {
        @{
            await Html.RenderPartialAsync("_ValidationScriptsPartial");
        }
    }
